                    <locus target="#79v" facs="084">Fol. 79v</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of secondary ownership, incomplete
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#24r #24v #28r #33v #35v" facs="028 029 032 038 040">Fols. 24r, 24v, 28r, 33v, 35v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#2v #6r #6v #11v #19r" facs="007 010 011 016 023">Fols. 2v, 6r, 6v, 11v, 19r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#14v" facs="019"> f. 14v, line 12</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#16r #25r #58r #77v #78r" facs="020 029 062 082 082">Fols. 16r, 25r, 58r, 77v, 78r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., erasure markings are visible;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <locus target="#11v #13r #17v #21v #27r" facs="016 017 022 026 031">Fols. 11v, 13r, 17v, 21v, 27r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <locus target="#132v #133r" facs="137">Fols. 132v, 133r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to complete the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line
                    </desc>
